Welcome to Link to Windows (hereinafter "the application") to synchronize your SMS, calls, contacts, app lists, photo albums and multimedia among your mobile phone, PC, and mobile devices. In the process, we need to get your wireless data (WLAN and cellular data) access, camera access, and the ability to access and read SMS, phone calls, contacts, app lists, photo albums, and multimedia on your phone. If you modify these data on one of your devices, the application will synchronize the changes to your other devices. We take industry-leading security technical measures to fully protect your personal information.

Please read the Application Privacy Statement, the Microsoft Privacy Statement and the Microsoft Service Agreement carefully to learn how Microsoft (hereinafter "we") ensure the safety of your personal information during the process of transmission and the relevant rights you own before commencing service.

The following terms require your attention:

You need a Microsoft account to use the application and synchronize data between your mobile devices and PC. For more information about Microsoft account, including the information saved to your account so that you can quickly access the info across products and devices, please read Your Microsoft account, your data, your choices.

You need to provide the name of your computer device and the app list to pair your phone with your computer. Otherwise, we will not be able to complete the pairing and provide the service to you.

You need to allow the application to access your wireless data (WLAN and cellular data) for transferring images and SMS among your phone, mobile devices, and computer. You can manage the access of the application through "[System Manager] - [Traffic Management] - [Application Networking]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check pictures and SMS on your computer or mobile devices.

You need to allow the application to access your camera to scan the QR code on your computer for pairing your phone with your computer and to access your phone's camera functionality on your Windows device. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [ Permissions] - [Camera]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to pair your phone with your computer by scanning the QR code from your phone or access your phone's camera functionality on your Windows device.

You need to allow the application to access your contacts for checking your phone's contact information on your computer and mobile devices. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Permissions] - [Contacts]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check your phone's contact information on your computer or mobile devices.

You need to allow the application to access your phone's SMS, calls and call history for checking or replying to your phone's SMS or make calls from your computer and mobile devices. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Permissions] - [SMS / Phone / Call History]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check or respond to SMS or calls from your phone on your computer or mobile devices.

The Application will ask permission to access your phone's photo albums and multimedia, which is necessary for transferring pictures and videos between your computer and your phone, you can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Permissions] - [Files and Media]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check the pictures and videos on your phone from your computers.

The Application will ask your permission to access your phone's screen on your computer, which is necessary for the Application to mirror the screen of your phone on your computer . If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to mirror the screen of your phone on your computer. When you start to mirror the screen of your phone on your computer, this application will ask permission to record audio so that it may stream your phone or app audio to your PC's speakers. If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to stream audio from your mirroring session. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Microphone permission]".

The Application will ask your permission to access the content you copy and paste, which is necessary for it to transfer these contents between your phone and computer, you can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Features] - [Cross-device copy and paste]". Some metadata will be transferred between devices each time content is copied on your phone and computer. If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to cross-device copy and paste content between your phone and your computer.

You need to allow the application to access your files to provide file management functionality on your Windows device. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Special App Access] - [All files access] - [Link to Windows]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to access your mobile device's file management functionality on your Windows device.

You need to allow the application to collect the application diagnostic data from your phone and other mobile devices, when you submit feedback to allow us to better understand your feedback. You can manage the collection of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Help us improve]". If you choose to turn off this collection, we will not allow to know how your devices are connected to each other. The diagnostic data from your computer will be automatically shared when and only when you provide feedback.

more
For further information on the scenarios in which the application will process your data, you should refer to the Microsoft Privacy Statement.

As a global service, [Link to Windows] uses a globally unified set of technical architecture. Therefore, pictures, SMS, videos, contacts, app lists, call history, and notifications on your phone will be transferred through Microsoft servers based outside of mainland China. We will not collect or store this data during the transfer process.

For information on the following, you should refer to the Application Privacy Statement:
1. our contact information,
2. the purposes, methods and types of processing of your personal information, and
3. the ways and procedures for exercising your rights.

If you need any support from us in using the application or need to send us any comments or suggestions, please contact us at Email: ltwfeedback@microsoft.com

You need to allow the application to access your camera to scan the QR code on your computer for pairing your mobile device with your computer and to access your mobile device's camera functionality on your Windows device. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [ Permissions] - [Camera]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to pair your mobile device with your computer by scanning the QR code from your mobile device or access your mobile device's camera functionality on your Windows device.

You need to allow the application to access your contacts for checking your mobile device's contact information on your computer. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Permissions] - [Contacts]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check your mobile device's contact information on your computer.

The Application will ask permission to access your mobile device's photo albums and multimedia, which is necessary for transferring pictures and videos between your computer and your mobile device, you can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Permissions] - [Files and Media]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to check the pictures and videos on your mobile device from your computers.

The Application will ask your permission to access your mobile device's screen on your computer, which is necessary for the Application to mirror the screen of your mobile device on your computer. If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to mirror the screen of your mobile device on your computer. When you start to mirror the screen of your mobile device on your computer, this application will ask permission to record audio so that it may stream your mobile device or app audio to your PC's speakers. If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to stream audio from your mirroring session. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Microphone permission]".

The Application will ask your permission to access the content you copy and paste, which is necessary for it to transfer these contents between your mobile device and computer, you can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Features] - [Cross-device copy and paste]". Some metadata will be transferred between devices each time content is copied on your mobile device and computer. If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to cross-device copy and paste content between your mobile device and your computer.

You need to allow the application to access your files to provide file management functionality on your Windows device. You can manage the access of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Special App Access] - [All files access] - [Link to Windows]". If you choose to turn off this access, you will not be able to access your mobile device's file management functionality on your Windows device.

You need to allow the application to collect the application diagnostic data from your mobile device, when you submit feedback to allow us to better understand your feedback. You can manage the collection of the application through "[Settings] - [Applications] - [Link to Windows] - [Help us improve]". If you choose to turn off this collection, we will not allow to know how your devices are connected to each other. The diagnostic data from your computer will be automatically shared when and only when you provide feedback.
